channel.title: WTF is up with my cd burner?
channel.description: Ok, so I've just gotten some songs I want to put on a disc, and So I paste them to h:\ then try to make a cd, only it says, please insert a blank cd! I've tried atleast the whole dam pack of cds, and when I put them in their nothing shows up on the disc. I know these cd's can burn because I just burned a couple of programs\music to them. So why the hell is it saying the cd's aren't blank. (The CD's are brand new, blank) I think its the cold but I'm not sure, If anyone knows and can help thanks.

item.dc:creator: @ilyaostr9 io9
item.description:
@ilyaostr9 wrote:

are they CD-R or CD-RW, cause usually, when you have drive letter access (directCD, Nero InCD, etc.) that’s only for CD-RW.

Try using Nero Burning ROM & New CD And paste the files to there…
